reviewText: I got this for a guy at work to give as a gift.  Great price. great series.

The best tv series in its time.  Really miss the family approved tv series and jag is fun for the whole family and not something you have to worry about your kids watching.  Also very gender friendly.  Pro military.  The wife loves it as well makes for great times as a family.  Prompts a lot of good what would you do in that situation questions.

I watched this series periodically over the years.  Because of my schedule I just could get to see most of the episodes. It's such a priviledge to own the entire series on DVD.  I watched the entire series over a month or so and it was just so great to see the great writing, acting, and thought (controversial subject topics) that went into every episode.  I wish it would have gone on even longer.
There were so many episodes that I often re-watch them because they are so good.

if you are a fan of military shows, david james elliott, or watched the show on tv or see the show in reruns,then you need to own the first nine seasons of jag. if you did not watch the show from the beggining like i did then this a good way to see the early episodes to see how it started for all involed on the show. its fun to watch how david and catherine interact with each other.if you are a fan of jag then you will also like ncis. can't wait for the last season of jag to come out.
This boxed set is a great value to receive all 9 seasons in one package.
JAG, NCIS  and all series by Bellisario are the ultimate BEST SHOWS on TV. Keep them coming.
